that there is no going back on heavy measures.)} 15. Kf1 (15. Ke2 c4 16. bxc4
bxc4 17. Bxc4 Rh4 18. d6 Rc8 19. Bxf7+ Kf8 {(and Black has Rxc2 and Qxg5.)})
15... Rh6 $1 16. d6 Rb8 {#(Now how on earth will White save the Ng5 or Bb2?)}
