more so as} (24... e6 25. g4 exf5 26. c3 Kc7 (26... fxg4 $4 27. Qxf6+) 27. g5
$1 {seemed impossibly difficult too.)}) 25. Re1 {
(Also 25.g4 proves very tough. I really would like to see a run from Fritz5.)}
25... e6 $5 {(A very nasty trap in which White falls, he had to play 26.Qf4+
to take away d2 from the Black Queen, in that case I don't see a win for Black,
but he played...)} 26. Rxe6 $2 Rxe6 27. Bxe6 Qd2 $1 {(White is in terminal
trouble but still manages to squeeze an endgame out of it.)} 28. g3 Re8 29.
Qf7+ Kb6 30. h4 Ka5 $5 {#(Black could have won the Be6 by Qd1+ and Qe2+, and
maybe this would have been the quicker course, in retrospect, because White
drums up some last nasty moves.)} 31. c3 Re7 $1 (31... Rxe6 $4 32. Qc7+ Rb6 33.
